The paper discusses the use of deep Graph Convolutional Networks (GCNs) and their application in point cloud semantic segmentation, which is a task commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also borrows concepts from Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are a popular machine learning technique, making it likely to be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) concepts such as semantic segmentation, which could lead to categorization under computational linguistics (cs.CL) as well. Finally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which could lead to categorization under neural networks (cs.NE).
